    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe one meta-question: Eric's proof seems to be as short as one can get, but it might be less \"readable\" insofar the other ones explictly mention <code>Finset.sum_eq_card_nsmul</code>or <code>Finset.sum_const</code>, which reveal what's happening. Are there any community standards or thoughts about this? My feeling is like in pen-and-paper math one optimizes more for comprehensibility that for length, but here a reader could just step in observing the goal changing and still get what's happening, just with perhaps more effort than if the code itself reveals everything</p>",
